Package: mosap
Type: Package
Version: 1.0.1
Title: Integrated Multi-Objective Spatial Action Planning            
Description: Description: Provides an exact multi-objective optimisation framework for integrated
    spatial action planning using mixed-integer programming (MIP). The package
    supports the design of management portfolios (e.g., conservation, restoration,
    and other interventions) across planning units to abate threats and satisfy
    user-defined constraints, while accounting for spatial structure (e.g.,
    connectivity and fragmentation). Multiple multi-objective methods are
    available, including weighted-sum aggregation, lexicographic (hierarchical)
    optimisation, epsilon-constraint, and AUGMECON-based approaches. Problems can
    be solved with commercial (e.g., Gurobi, CPLEX) and open-source (e.g., CBC,
    SYMPHONY) MIP solvers. Methods build on Salgado-Rojas et al. (2020)
    <doi:10.1016/j.ecolmodel.2019.108901>, Beyer et al. (2016)
    <doi:10.1016/j.ecolmodel.2016.02.005>, Cattarino et al. (2015)
    <doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0128027>, and Watts et al. (2009)
    <doi:10.1016/j.envsoft.2009.06.005>.
